AWS CLI Installation on Linux
-----------------------------

1. Update the System (recommended)
   For Debian/Ubuntu:
     sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
   For RHEL/CentOS:
     sudo yum update -y

2. Download the AWS CLI v2 Installer
   curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

3. Unzip the Installer
   unzip awscliv2.zip
   If unzip is not installed:
     Debian/Ubuntu: sudo apt install unzip
     RHEL/CentOS:   sudo yum install unzip

4. Run the Install Script
   sudo ./aws/install

5. Verify the Installation
   aws --version

Expected Output (version may vary):
   aws-cli/2.x.x Python/3.x.x Linux/x86_64 source

